    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-10T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-10T22:00:00-05:00" n="601"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d601">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115 Radio Corporation of America/18:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1"
                            type="from">Cunningham</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-11T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 11, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 11—2:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>179. Department’s telegram No. 69, March 3, 10 a.m., regarding radio station.
                    Withdrawal of Chinese forces has left radio station well within Japanese
                    military lines. I understand chief question now is repair of power lines and
                    connections with radio central office in Settlement. On March 5th and March 7th
                    at request of <persName corresp="#p_SGF1">Shecklen</persName> I made
                    representations to Japanese Consul General asking that facilities be accorded to
                    enable these repairs to be made as rapidly as possible. <pb facs="0666" n="562"
                        xml:id="pg_562"/>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SGF1">Shecklen</persName> informs me that Japanese are
                    granting such facilities for repair work as could reasonably be expected under
                    the circumstances. He is keeping Radio Corporation fully informed.</p>
                <p>Not repeated to the Legation. Copy to the Minister.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CES1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
